# Project refactor TODO — history preparers

Goal: extract duplicated logic between file-mode and repo-mode history
preparers into small, testable helper methods. For each helper:

- implement helper in the indicated class
- update one `_prep` function to use it
- run `scripts/test_prep_backends.py ../test-repo` and `scripts/check_axioms.py`
- when green, update the corresponding other preparer to use it and test again

Workflow: go slowly, one helper at a time. Mark items as done as tests pass.

- [x] 1. Add `AppBase._run_git_lines(cmd: list[str], label: str|None) -> list[str]`
      - implemented and used by preparers; tests updated

- [x] 2. Add `AppBase._canonical_relpath(path: str, repo_root: str) -> str`
      - implemented (normalizes to realpath)

- [x] 3. Add `AppBase._compute_pseudo_timestamps(repo_root: str, mods: list[str], single_path: str) -> (mods_ts, staged_ts)`
      - implemented: computes latest mtime for `mods` or a single path, plus `.git/index` mtime

- [x] 4. Add `AppBase._format_pseudo_summary(pseudo_entries: list[tuple[str,str]])`
      - implemented: central helper appends pseudo-summary rows and attaches metadata

- [x] 5. Add `AppBase._parse_git_log_lines(lines: list[str]) -> list[tuple[datetime,str,str]]`
      - implemented: robust parsing for `git log --pretty=format:%H\t%aI\t%s` lines

- [x] 6. Add `HistoryListBase._format_commit_row(dt: datetime, hash: str, msg: str) -> str`
      - implemented: centralized commit row formatting used by history preparers

- [x] 7. Add `AppBase._append_file_row(display: str, full_path: str, is_dir: bool=False, status: str|None=None)`
      - implemented: appends ListItem and attaches `_raw_text`, `_filename`, `_is_dir`, optional `_repo_status`

- [x] 8. Add `HistoryListBase._finalize_prep(curr_hash: str|None, prev_hash: str|None, path: str|None)`
      - implemented: centralized post-prep highlight/marking and app-state sync

- [x] 9. Replace duplicated parity scaffolding with `AppBase._compare_backends`
      - implemented: central comparison + logging helper and test delegator

- [x] 10. Run full regression: `scripts/test_prep_backends.py ../test-repo` and `scripts/check_axioms.py`.
      - executed: parity tests show 0 diffs; axiom checker OK

- [x] 11. Add docstrings to small safe helpers and logger
      - implemented: `_logger_trace` and `_safe_*` wrappers documented

Next tasks (suggested)

- [x] 12. Refactor preparers to consistently call `HistoryListBase._finalize_prep` at end of prep functions
      - Updated `FileModeHistoryList.prepFileModeHistoryList` to call `_finalize_prep` and ran tests (parity/axioms OK)

- [x] 13. Small improvements to `_append_file_row` formatting and status markers
      - Implemented: `_append_file_row` now applies `MARKERS` and status-based `STYLE_*` formatting; tests run OK

- [x] 14. Consider extracting more test helpers into `scripts/test_prep_backends.py::Dummy` for parity coverage

Notes:

- Follow the one-helper → update-one-prep → run-tests discipline.
- When adding helpers that tests may exercise, add delegators to the `Dummy` class in `scripts/test_prep_backends.py`.

After every modification, run these checkers:

```bash
python3 scripts/test_prep_backends.py ../test-repo
python3 scripts/check_axioms.py
```

